Pre-Game Insights: LeBron James and Anthony Davis shone for LA, tallying 19 points, five rebounds, four assists and two blocks in 16 minutes, and 17 points, eight rebounds and three assists respectively.
Durant, Booker, and Beal struggled for the Suns, with Durant producing six points on 3 of 10 shots, Booker having 12, and Beal scoring 11.
The Lakers enter this contest as the underdogs.
LeBron James underperformed, tallying six points on 3 of 9 shots, while Anthony Davis was the only bright spot after putting up 24 points and 12 rebounds on 10 of 14 shots.
The Suns are coming off an impressive 118-114 win over the Nuggets despite playing their bench and reserves only with Kevin Durant, Bradley Beal, Devin Booker and other starters resting/injured.
